itable plainrowheaders\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Venue\n! Ref.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2007}}\n| [[Finlandia Hall]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/music-eurovision-dc-idUSN0330320720070304|title=Finland prepares for its Eurovision close-up|date=March 4, 2007|via=www.reuters.com|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}\n| [[Palace of Serbia]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/palata-srbije-gets-ready-for-opening-party|title=Palata Srbije gets ready for opening party|website=eurovision.tv|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]|date=18 May 2008|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2009}}\n| [[Moscow Manege|Central Manezh Exhibition Center]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2009/05/11/eurovision-2009s-grand-opening-a1342|title=Eurovision 2009's Grand Opening|date=May 11, 2009|website=The Moscow Times|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2010}}\n| [[Oslo City Hall]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/oslo-welcomes-the-stars|title=Oslo welcomes the stars!|website=eurovision.tv|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]|date=23 May 2010|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2011}}\n| [[Tonhalle D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eurovision.tv/story/tonight-opening-reception-takes-place-in-duesseldorf|title=Tonight: Opening Reception takes place in D\u00fcsseldorf|date=May 7, 2011|website=eurovision.tv|publisher=[[European Broadcasting Union]]}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2012}}\n| [[Baku Sports Palace]]\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azertag.az/en/xeber/Light_your_fireEurovision_2012_Opening_ceremony_to_be_held_in_Euroclub-222312?__cf_chl_jschl_tk__=678537a625fb6fbcb55707a6d9849d040a126804-1584638111-0-AavbAYzrYHRHULiZeDTVu2iuGeK_xTriN9et6kmetvcta1YgbWeSEHvg_wy3RAVTYTyu4_ajYAZ73GVyx4Uz8YSov5hiqwWhDedtQQcq7611DtgCs9Q1N3CBw4QRosn57-Lg42lvR3GiBw1c2ZoBSj24cFn8XRYNuYhPgHB7uQnwEI55ApapP