by Lizzo]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs number-one singles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2016 single by Lizzo}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Good as Hell\n| cover      = Lizzo - Good as Hell.png\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Lizzo]]\n| EP         = [[Coconut Oil (EP)|Coconut Oil]]\n| released   = March 8, 2016\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre      = <!--Please source genres -->\n| length     = 2:39\n| label      =\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n* Nice Life\n| writer     =\n* [[Lizzo|Melissa Jefferson]]\n* [[Ricky Reed|Eric Frederic]]\n| producer   = [[Ricky Reed]]\n| prev_title = Basement Queens\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = Phone\n| next_year  = 2016\n| misc = {{External music video|{{YouTube|SmbmeOgWsqE|\"Good as Hell\" (2016 version)}}}} {{External music video|{{YouTube|vuq-VAiW9kw|\"Good as Hell\" (2019 version)}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Good as Hell'''\" is a song recorded by American singer and rapper [[Lizzo]]. It was released on October 7, 2016, through [[Atlantic Records]] and Nice Life Recording Company as the [[lead single]] from her debut [[extended play]] ''[[Coconut Oil (EP)|Coconut Oil]]'', but then re-released in 2019 as a radio single, where it became a [[sleeper hit]] like her first hit, \"[[Truth Hurts (song)|Truth Hurts]]\". It was written by Lizzo and [[Ricky Reed]] and produced by Reed. The song subsequently served as the namesake for her 2017 Good as Hell Tour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blacdetroit.com/BLAC-Detroit/May-2017/Lizzo-wants-to-make-Detroit-feel-Good-As-Hell/|title=Lizzo wants to make Detroit feel 'Good As Hell'|last=Espy|first=Jasmine|date=June 1, 2017|website=blacdetroit.com|access-date=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n\"Good as Hell\" was originally recorded for the soundtrack of the 2016 film ''[[Barbershop: The Next Cut]].'' It first made its premiere on [[Zane Lowe]]'s [[Beats 1 Radio]] show.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spin.com/2016/03/lizzo-good-as-hell-new-song-beats-1-zane-lowe-barbershop-3/|title=Lizzo Drops New Ricky Reed-Produced Banger, 'Good As Hell'|last=Carley|first=Brennan|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=March 7, 2016|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe song was released to digital retailers and streaming platforms on March 8, 2016.<ref name=\"Single\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/good-as-hell-single/1090585451|title=Good As Hell \u2013 Single by Lizzo on Apple Music|website=Apple Music|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> A four-track dance remix EP was released on June 17, 2016.<ref name=\"Remix EP\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/good-as-hell-remixes-ep/1122219745|title=Good As Hell (Remixes) \u2013 EP by Lizzo on Apple Music|website=Apple Music|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAn official remix featuring American singer [[Ariana Grande]] was released on October 25, 2019.<ref name=\"IHeartRadio\">{{cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-10-24-ariana-grandes-remix-of-lizzos-good-as-hell-is-dropping-tonight/|title=Ariana Grande's Remix Of Lizzo's 'Good As Hell' Is Dropping Tonight|last=Brooks|first=Hayden|website=iheartradio.com|date=October 24, 2019|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music videos==\nThe first music video was released on May 11, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SmbmeOgWsqE|title=Good As Hell by Lizzo on YouTube|via=YouTube|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> It features Lizzo and multiple women of color going to a [[hair salon]], getting their hair and nails done while having fun with the occasion. The music video also ties into the movie ''[[Barbershop: The Next Cut]]''.<ref name=\"GoodMusicVideo\">{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/2067366/lizzo-good-as-hell-video/video/|title=Lizzo \u2013 \u201cGood As Hell\u201d Video|publisher=Stereogum}}</ref>\n\nOn December 9, 2019, in the wake of the song's growing popularity, a new \"official music video\" was premiered on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vuq-VAiW9kw|title=Good As Hell (Official Music Video) by Lizzo on YouTube|via=YouTube|accessdate=December 9, 2019}}</ref> This music video, directed by [[Alan Ferguson (director)|Alan Ferguson]], is set in [[Southern University]], and also features the Baton Rouge HBCU.<ref name=\"GoodMusicVideo\" /> In it, the university's marching band students have trouble with some regular classes in between preparation for an upcoming performance, with one of the university's marching band dancers looking heartbroken over a prior relationship she had with another student. Lizzo then shows up during one of the rehearsals and appears with the group throughout the video, performing her song and having fun with the group throughout the video.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/lizzo-good-as-hell-video-new-marching-band-923476/|title=Lizzo Joins Southern University\u2019s Marching Band for New \u2018Good as Hell\u2019 Video|publisher=Rolling Stone|date=December 9, 2019|accessdate=December 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nIn a review for [[National Public Radio|NPR]], Hanif Abdurraqib praised the song's inspirational and motivational qualities, saying \"[the song is] the anthem of both the night itself and of life in preparation for it: the saint that comes to you in the mirror when the lighting is bad, or the hair won't move the way you want it to, or when you've tried on all of the outfits and none of them seem right.\" Abdurraqib also called it \"the rare song that can play at any point in a night out and resonate in each.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/11/28/671236822/lizzo-good-as-hell-american-anthem|title=In Praise Of 'Good As Hell,' The Song That Believes In You Even When You Don't|last=Abdurraqib|first=Hanif|publisher=[[NPR]]|date=November 28, 2018|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' included \"Good as Hell\" on their list of the Top 10 Lizzo songs, saying \"the song's message of self-love mixed with a melody that will worm its way inside your head make this track an absolute stunner.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8511471/lizzo-best-songs|title=Lizzo's 10 Best Songs: Critic's Picks|last=Daw|first=Stephen|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=May 14, 2019|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\nWhile \"Good as Hell\" never charted during ''Coconut Oil''{{'}}s release period, it began to gain traction in 2019 following Lizzo's continuing career trajectory and the chart climb of her 2017 hit \"[[Truth Hurts (song)|Truth Hurts]]\". Following Lizzo's performance of the song at the [[2019 MTV Video Music Awards]], it entered the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] the following week at number 52, later peaking at number three, becoming Lizzo's second top 10 hit on the chart.<ref name=\"Hot 100\"/><ref name=\"Hot 100 peak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8544750/post-malone-circles-number-one-hot-100|title=Post Malone's 'Circles' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Billie Eilish's 'Everything I Wanted' Blasts to Top 10|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 26, 2019}}</ref> \n\nThe club mixes of \"Good as Hell\" gave Lizzo her first number one at [[Dance Club Songs]] and her second chart topper at [[Dance/Mix Show Airplay]] in December 2019.<ref>[https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545529/lizzo-good-as-hell-tops-dance-charts \"Lizzo's 'Good as Hell' Leaps to No. 1 on 2 Dance Charts\"] from ''Billboard'' (December 5, 2019)</ref>\n\nFollowing the release of the remix featuring Ariana Grande, \"Good as Hell\" reached new top 10 peaks in the United Kingdom,  New Zealand, and Australia, becoming Lizzo's first top 10 single in each of these countries.\n\n==In other media==\n\"Good as Hell\" has been featured in the films ''[[Barbershop: The Next Cut]]'', ''[[A Bad Moms Christmas]]'', ''[[I Feel Pretty (film)|I Feel Pretty]]'', ''[[Blockers (film)|Blockers]]'' and ''[[Brittany Runs a Marathon]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/11/28/671236822/lizzo-good-as-hell-american-anthem|title=In Praise Of 'Good As Hell,' The Song That Believes In You Even When You Don't|last=Abdurraqib|first=Hanif|publisher=NPR|date=November 28, 2019|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> as well as successive adverts for [[N Brown Group|JD Williams]] and ''[[My Little Pony: Pony Life]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/charts-analysis-sheeran-and-stormzy-still-on-top/077575|title=Charts analysis: Sheeran and Stormzy still on top|last=Jones|first=Alan|date=September 26, 2019|work=[[Music Week]]|accessdate=October 6, 2019|quote=First released in 2016, Good As Hell became better known as the bed to a JD Williams TV commercial, and nibbled at the chart earlier this year.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/11/13/my-little-pony-pony-life-first-look-lizzo/|title=My Little Pony to launch new animated series and toy line \u2014 see exclusive first look|last=Aquilina|first=Tyler|date=November 13, 2019|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=December 3, 2019|quote=The video above offers an exclusive first look at both the new toys and the newly designed animated characters, set (appropriately if somewhat oddly) to Lizzo\u2018s \u201cGood as Hell.\u201d}}</ref> It was also used in [[RuPaul's Drag Race (season 10)|Season 10]] of the television show ''[[RuPaul's Drag Race]]'' in \"lip sync for your life\" between [[Kameron Michaels]] and [[Mon\u00e9t X Change]]. Lizzo herself served as a guest judge in the episode.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/thepitch/rupauls-drag-race-has-lost-its-free-queer-spirit-in-its-lip-sync-songs/|title='RuPaul's Drag Race' Has Lost Its Free Queer Spirit in Its Lip Sync Songs|last=Pitre|first=Jake|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=June 29, 2019|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nLizzo performed the song on ''[[Saturday Night Live (season 45)|Saturday Night Live]]'' on December 21, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/lizzo-slays-saturday-night-live-musical-debut-with-festive-performances-of-truth-hurts-and-good-as|title='Lizzo Slays 'Saturday Night Live' Musical Debut With Festive Performances of 'Truth Hurts' and 'Good As Hell'|last=Seemayer|first=Zach|website=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|date=December 22, 2019|accessdate=December 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n'''Digital download'''<ref name=\"Single\"/>\n# \"Good as Hell\" \u2013 2:39\n\n'''Spotify version'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/album/4CA8GvVF7swZafg0zYh9qq|title=Good as Hell . Lizzo|date=March 9, 2016}}</ref>\n# \"Good as Hell\" \u2013 2:39\n# \"Truth Hurts\" \u2013 2:53\n\n'''Digital Remix EP'''<ref name=\"Remix EP\"/>\n# \"Good as Hell\" ([[Bad Royale]] Remix) \u2013 3:33\n# \"Good as Hell\" (Nick Catchdubs Remix) \u2013 3:56\n# \"Good as Hell\" (BNDR Remix) \u2013 3:43\n# \"Good as Hell\" (Two Stacks Remix) \u2013 2:57\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|6|artist=Lizzo|song=Good as Hell|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia Urban ([[Australian Recording Industry Association|ARIA]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cdn.aria.com.au/pdfs/40F1405AA5D7C0456D4FBE2C2E70EFDBED1B410567EF5E5737D6A31C16B5643D/ARIA%20Urban%20Singles%20Chart.pdf?seq=26|title=ARIA Top 40 Urban Singles Chart|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|accessdate=November 11, 2019}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|62|artist=Lizzo|song=Good as Hell|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 7, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Fland