ird Al\" Yankovic]]\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Work\n! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 2013 || [[Writers Guild of America Award]]<ref>Mitchell, Gregg; Strell, Jay (December 6, 2012). [http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=5098 \"2013 ''Writers Guild Awards'' Television, News, Radio, Promotional Writing, and Graphic Animation Nominees Announced\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303232741/http://www.wga.org/content/default.aspx?id=5098 |date=March 3, 2016 }}. [[Writers Guild of America]]</ref> || [[Writers Guild of America Awards 2012#Comedy/Variety (including talk) series|Best Comedy/Variety (Including Talk) - Series]] || rowspan=13|''[[Key & Peele]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\"|<center>[[Peabody Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peabodyawards.com/stories/story/2013-peabody-winners|title=The Peabody Awards|publisher=[[Peabody Award]]s|accessdate=May 9, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508204320/http://peabodyawards.com/stories/story/2013-peabody-winners|archivedate=May 8, 2016}}</ref></center> || {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=5| 2014 || [[NAACP Image Award]]<ref name=\"THRNIA45\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/naacp-image-awards-winners-682585|title=NAACP Image Awards: The Winners|first1=Aaron |last1=Couch|first2= Arlene|last2= Washington|date=February 22, 2014|accessdate=February 22, 2014|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|url-status=live|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160313195908/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/naacp-image-awards-winners-682585|archivedate=March 13, 2016}}</ref> || Outstanding Variety\u2013Series or Special || {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[American Comedy Award]]<ref name=\"EWACA\">{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2014/05/09/amy-poehler-seth-rogen-american-comedy-awards/|title=Amy Poehler, Seth Rogen win American Comedy Awards|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 9, 2014|accessdate=Septe